==Old English==
===Etymology===
From Germanic ''*swēsa-'' ‘own, relation’, Indo-European.  Cognate with Old Frisian [[swes|swēs]] ‘related’, Old Saxon [[swas|swās]] ‘dear’, Old Norse [[sváss]] ‘dear, trusty’, Gothic [[𐍃𐍅𐌴𐍃]] ‘own’.  The IE root is also the source of Latin [[sibi]], Russian [[себя]].

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /swæ:s/

===Adjective===
'''swǣs'''
# [[dear]], [[beloved]]
# [[own]]

